---
/**
 * rest-api/0009 · Figure 4 — "the observability triad, stitched by one id": logs
 * (structured JSON), metrics (RED), and traces (OpenTelemetry) all tied together
 * by a propagated correlation / request id (traceparent · X-Request-Id).
 *
 * Copied VERBATIM from docs/rest-api/lessons/0009-error-design-rate-limiting-observability.html
 * (figure + svg + figcaption). Lives as an .astro component for the
 * kebab-case-SVG reason. Markers (#arw, #arwA, #arwG) come from the source's
 * global hidden <svg>, inlined here in a local <defs>, fills/ids verbatim.
 */
---

<figure>
    <svg
        viewBox="0 0 600 230"
        role="img"
        aria-label="The observability triad: logs, metrics, and traces, all stitched together by one correlation or request id flowing through every service"
    >
        <defs>
            <marker
                id="arw"
                viewBox="0 0 10 10"
                refX="8.5"
                refY="5"
                markerWidth="7"
                markerHeight="7"
                orient="auto-start-reverse"
                ><path d="M0,0 L10,5 L0,10 z" fill="#6b675f"></path></marker
            >
            <marker
                id="arwA"
                viewBox="0 0 10 10"
                refX="8.5"
                refY="5"
                markerWidth="7"
                markerHeight="7"
                orient="auto-start-reverse"
                ><path d="M0,0 L10,5 L0,10 z" fill="#7a1f12"></path></marker
            >
            <marker
                id="arwG"
                viewBox="0 0 10 10"
                refX="8.5"
                refY="5"
                markerWidth="7"
                markerHeight="7"
                orient="auto-start-reverse"
                ><path d="M0,0 L10,5 L0,10 z" fill="#2f5d3a"></path></marker
            >
        </defs>
        <g font-family="ui-sans-serif,system-ui,sans-serif">
            <text
                x="300"
                y="18"
                text-anchor="middle"
                font-size="12"
                font-weight="700"
                fill="#111110">THE OBSERVABILITY TRIAD, STITCHED BY ONE ID</text
            >
            <!-- central id -->
            <rect x="210" y="96" width="180" height="44" rx="22" fill="#1c1b18" stroke="#1c1b18"
            ></rect>
            <text
                x="300"
                y="115"
                text-anchor="middle"
                font-size="11"
                font-weight="700"
                fill="#f3efe3">correlation / request id</text
            >
            <text
                x="300"
                y="130"
                text-anchor="middle"
                font-size="8.5"
                font-family="ui-monospace,monospace"
                fill="#e8b3a6">traceparent · X-Request-Id</text
            >
            <!-- logs -->
            <rect x="20" y="40" width="160" height="58" rx="9" fill="#eef5ee" stroke="#2f5d3a"
            ></rect>
            <text
                x="100"
                y="62"
                text-anchor="middle"
                font-size="11"
                font-weight="700"
                fill="#2f5d3a">LOGS</text
            >
            <text x="100" y="79" text-anchor="middle" font-size="9" fill="#244a2e"
                >structured JSON</text
            >
            <text x="100" y="91" text-anchor="middle" font-size="8.5" fill="#6b675f"
                >not free-text</text
            >
            <!-- metrics -->
            <rect x="220" y="174" width="160" height="56" rx="9" fill="#eef2f5" stroke="#1f3a5a"
            ></rect>
            <text
                x="300"
                y="196"
                text-anchor="middle"
                font-size="11"
                font-weight="700"
                fill="#1f3a5a">METRICS · RED</text
            >
            <text x="300" y="212" text-anchor="middle" font-size="9" fill="#1f3a5a"
                >Rate · Errors · Duration</text
            >
            <text x="300" y="224" text-anchor="middle" font-size="8.5" fill="#6b675f"
                >duration = p50/p95/p99</text
            >
            <!-- traces -->
            <rect x="420" y="40" width="160" height="58" rx="9" fill="#fbfaf2" stroke="#7a1f12"
            ></rect>
            <text
                x="500"
                y="62"
                text-anchor="middle"
                font-size="11"
                font-weight="700"
                fill="#7a1f12">TRACES</text
            >
            <text x="500" y="79" text-anchor="middle" font-size="9" fill="#2c2a26"
                >OpenTelemetry</text
            >
            <text x="500" y="91" text-anchor="middle" font-size="8.5" fill="#6b675f"
                >where time goes</text
            >
            <!-- connectors -->
            <line x1="180" y1="86" x2="214" y2="104" stroke="#2f5d3a" marker-end="url(#arwG)"
            ></line>
            <line x1="420" y1="86" x2="386" y2="104" stroke="#7a1f12" marker-end="url(#arwA)"
            ></line>
            <line x1="300" y1="140" x2="300" y2="172" stroke="#1f3a5a" marker-end="url(#arw)"
            ></line>
        </g>
    </svg>
    <figcaption>
        One id flows through every service, so logs, RED metrics, and OpenTelemetry traces all point
        at the <em>same</em> request. Define <strong>SLOs and error budgets</strong> so "page someone?"
        has a numeric answer, not a vibe.
    </figcaption>
</figure>
